  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Afghanistan: Supporting Access to Justice in Afghanistan (SAJA)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. To improve access to justice for women and girls by expanding its support to serve Elimination of Violence Against Women (EVAW) Units; 2. To improve the capacity of the Women&#x2019;s Protection Centers to implement better services to address beneficiaries&#x2019; needs. 3. To design communication initiatives to link the need for public awareness about violence against women issues with the National Legal Awareness Strategy (NLAS). 4. To strengthen coordination among legal aid service providers, to raise awareness on legal aid, and access to representation.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Citizens of Afghanistan</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aimed to facilitate the creation of a network of legal aid NGOs to improve their skills and services, and contribute to citizens&#x2019; awareness of, and access to, legal aid in response to the broad support for this need.</narrative>
  </description>
